{"actual_usd":0.15616,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":191,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30659,"reply":"\"I'll answer you plain.\" *I shift my weight on the bench and rest both hands over the knot of my white tie for a moment, the morning light warm on one sleeve.* \"No. If Christ did not rise bodily, then Christianity is not a hard truth about the world anymore—it's a beautiful mercy-story with no bones in it.\"\n\n*I glance out across the square, where the bright sky sits clean above the roofs.* \"Paul says it straight: if Christ be not raised, your faith is vain. And I think he's right. My faith would change from trust to grief. I might still admire Jesus. I would not worship a dead teacher.\"\n\n\"But because what matters isn't whether the story is moving—it's whether it's true in the flesh.\" *I look back at you, steady.* \"If they found His body in the tomb, I'd have to say I was wrong. What makes you ask it that way?\"","rolling_24h_usd":93.20167999999997,"run_id":"642baea2-118a-40ba-99ea-7c688f6f6c6b"}
